1
00:00:05,253 --> 00:00:09,782
The opposition; it’s providing
nourishment to the līlā.

2
00:00:10,491 --> 00:00:13,054
[Jesus and Judas]

3
00:00:13,928 --> 00:00:19,893
Nārada, we see,
instigating opposition, at times.

4
00:00:19,920 --> 00:00:23,576
When Kaṁsa’s ready
to let the whole thing go

5
00:00:23,576 --> 00:00:27,732
and Nārada’s thinking,
“Oh, then Kṛṣṇa … it will be delayed,

6
00:00:27,732 --> 00:00:29,648
it’ll delay Kṛṣṇa’s appearing”,

7
00:00:29,648 --> 00:00:34,079
and he makes Kaṁsa paranoid

8
00:00:34,710 --> 00:00:40,155
to more quickly
bring the descent of Kṛṣṇa.

9
00:00:40,832 --> 00:00:44,942
Nīmai Paṇḍit faces opposition
in Nabadwīp

10
00:00:44,942 --> 00:00:50,484
that brings him to the point
of taking sannyās

11
00:00:51,345 --> 00:00:56,041
and disseminating
the Kṛṣṇa consciousness movement.

12
00:00:56,287 --> 00:01:00,397
So sometimes
Guru Mahārāj will say, “contrast”—

13
00:01:00,397 --> 00:01:04,274
to contrast 
what is genuinely spiritual.

14
00:01:05,458 --> 00:01:09,442
Sometimes we would see
something in the Dhām

15
00:01:09,765 --> 00:01:15,813
that so much contradicts
our stereotype of the Dhām,

16
00:01:15,813 --> 00:01:18,872
that we’re bewildered.

17
00:01:19,241 --> 00:01:22,623
Guru Mahārāj is saying
that’s for contrast,

18
00:01:22,623 --> 00:01:26,620
to make you think what really
is spiritual substance,

19
00:01:26,620 --> 00:01:30,005
who really is a Dhām-basi,

20
00:01:30,005 --> 00:01:33,220
what really is a holy place.

21
00:01:34,113 --> 00:01:39,321
So, itarataś cā,
directly and indirectly.

22
00:01:39,321 --> 00:01:43,896
Same thing in the nutshell ślokas
of the Bhāgavatam.

23
00:01:43,896 --> 00:01:51,337
The indirect has its place;
the opposition has its place.

24
00:01:52,764 --> 00:01:56,405
But Śiva’s complaining
a little bit,

25
00:01:56,405 --> 00:02:01,758
“Why do I always have to do this?”
this type of sevā.

26
00:02:01,758 --> 00:02:08,197
Māyāvādi-bhāṣya śunile
haya sarva-nāśa [Cc: 2.6.169]

27
00:02:11,427 --> 00:02:15,426
Guru Mahārāj will say,
“Who could be entrusted

28
00:02:15,426 --> 00:02:20,117
to do such a thing 
but who’s most dear?”

29
00:02:20,117 --> 00:02:25,847
When he was parsing
the betrayal of Jesus by Judas,

30
00:02:26,274 --> 00:02:29,638
and then Jesus is carrying
the cross and stops,

31
00:02:29,638 --> 00:02:34,779
Veronica’s wiping his face,
looks, Judas is there,

32
00:02:34,779 --> 00:02:38,908
and some look transpires
between Christ and Judas,

33
00:02:38,908 --> 00:02:41,974
and Judas goes off 
and hangs himself.

34
00:02:42,451 --> 00:02:43,451
So generally people think,

35
00:02:43,451 --> 00:02:46,735
“Oh, he felt so much guilt 
for what he’d done—

36
00:02:46,735 --> 00:02:50,686
betrayed his lord
for thirty pieces of silver”,

37
00:02:51,733 --> 00:02:54,744
but Guru Mahārāj gave
another explanation.

38
00:02:55,097 --> 00:03:03,329
He said when they make eye contact,
the Christ is conveying to him,

39
00:03:03,329 --> 00:03:08,997
“Forgive me
for using you like this.

40
00:03:10,028 --> 00:03:18,770
Forgive me for making your name black
for all time to come.”

41
00:03:20,032 --> 00:03:23,043
So out of necessity of līlā …
 

42
00:03:24,543 --> 00:03:26,103
And the conclusion:
 

43
00:03:26,103 --> 00:03:30,132
who could be entrusted 
with this type of sevā

44
00:03:30,132 --> 00:03:34,690
but someone very intimate, 
near, and dear?

